{
  "video_id": "FXfrncRey-4",
  "title": "The ULTRAVIOLET CATASTROPHE",
  "es": 1,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 2670.0,
      "end_time": 4520.0,
      "text": "Over 100 years\nago, physicists were"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 4520.0,
      "end_time": 7250.0,
      "text": "trying to figure\nout how things glow,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 7250.0,
      "end_time": 10210.0,
      "text": "like molten glass or hot lava."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 10210.0,
      "end_time": 12120.0,
      "text": "It seems like a simple\nquestion and was"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 12120.0,
      "end_time": 14330.0,
      "text": "being pondered by\nsuch physicists"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 14330.0,
      "end_time": 17130.0,
      "text": "as Lord Rayleigh at the\nturn of the 20th century."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 17130.0,
      "end_time": 21210.0,
      "text": "I give you a wooden skewer\nthat, when touched to a flame,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 21210.0,
      "end_time": 23720.0,
      "text": "glows orange-red."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 23720.0,
      "end_time": 25910.0,
      "text": "Rayleigh knew that\nthe color of this glow"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 25910.0,
      "end_time": 28430.0,
      "text": "depends on temperature,\nlike the sun that"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 28430.0,
      "end_time": 32280.0,
      "text": "has a surface temperature of\n5,500 degrees Celsius radiates"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 32280.0,
      "end_time": 35900.0,
      "text": "a bunch of different colors\nthat together look white to us."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 35900.0,
      "end_time": 40260.0,
      "text": "Or me-- at 37 degrees Celsius,\nI have this invisible halo"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 40260.0,
      "end_time": 41660.0,
      "text": "of infrared light."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 41660.0,
      "end_time": 42540.0,
      "text": "Fun fact."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 42540.0,
      "end_time": 44830.0,
      "text": "Infrared light is\ninvisible to humans,"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 44830.0,
      "end_time": 48110.0,
      "text": "but snakes can actually sense\nit from up to a meter away"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 48110.0,
      "end_time": 49740.0,
      "text": "to detect prey."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 49740.0,
      "end_time": 52374.0,
      "text": "Rayleigh wanted to understand\nwhere the light came from"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 52374.0,
      "end_time": 53790.0,
      "text": "and come up with\na rule that would"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 53790.0,
      "end_time": 56820.0,
      "text": "predict how much of each\ncolor it would emit."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 56820.0,
      "end_time": 58680.0,
      "text": "This is its spectrum."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 58680.0,
      "end_time": 59630.0,
      "text": "Another fun fact."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 59630.0,
      "end_time": 62370.0,
      "text": "Lord Rayleigh was the guy who\nfigured out, mathematically,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 62370.0,
      "end_time": 64150.0,
      "text": "why the sky is blue."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 64150.00000000001,
      "end_time": 66760.0,
      "text": "So Rayleigh thought of the\nsimplest possible object,"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 66760.0,
      "end_time": 68920.0,
      "text": "something that\nabsorbs all light."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 68920.0,
      "end_time": 71950.0,
      "text": "Objects absorb, emit,\nand reflect light."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 71950.0,
      "end_time": 75350.0,
      "text": "Rayleigh's object would only\nabsorb and emit, but not"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 75350.0,
      "end_time": 76080.0,
      "text": "reflect."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 76080.0,
      "end_time": 77830.0,
      "text": "So all you would see\nwhen you look at it"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 77830.0,
      "end_time": 80190.0,
      "text": "is its glow or its radiation."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 80190.0,
      "end_time": 82320.0,
      "text": "Physicists call\nthis a blackbody."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 82320.0,
      "end_time": 85690.0,
      "text": "Technically, a blackbody\nisn't black, it's glowing."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 85690.0,
      "end_time": 87890.0,
      "text": "But whatever, physicists."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 87890.0,
      "end_time": 90530.0,
      "text": "A true blackbody doesn't\nexist in real life"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 90530.0,
      "end_time": 92550.0,
      "text": "because nothing\nabsorbs all light"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 92550.0,
      "end_time": 95390.0,
      "text": "and radiates perfectly,\nalthough stars like the sun"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 95390.0,
      "end_time": 96594.0,
      "text": "come pretty close."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 96594.0,
      "end_time": 98510.0,
      "text": "Kind of funny, right,\nthat the brightest thing"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 98510.0,
      "end_time": 100690.0,
      "text": "we know in our solar\nsystem is the closest thing"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 100690.0,
      "end_time": 102430.0,
      "text": "we know to a blackbody."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 102430.0,
      "end_time": 103510.0,
      "text": "Physicists."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 103510.0,
      "end_time": 105980.0,
      "text": "Anyway, at that time,\nphysicists didn't really"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 105980.0,
      "end_time": 108346.0,
      "text": "understand atoms and molecules."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 108346.0,
      "end_time": 110220.0,
      "text": "They thought everything\nwas made of particles"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 110220.0,
      "end_time": 112110.0,
      "text": "that vibrate like springs."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 112110.0,
      "end_time": 113970.0,
      "text": "Rayleigh and his\ncolleague, James Jeans,"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 113970.0,
      "end_time": 117210.0,
      "text": "imagined a blackbody made\nof these vibrating particles"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 117210.0,
      "end_time": 119090.0,
      "text": "where the vibration\nwas continuously"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 119090.0,
      "end_time": 120190.0,
      "text": "converted to light."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 120190.0,
      "end_time": 122020.0,
      "text": "From that model, they\ncame up with a rule"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 122020.0,
      "end_time": 125060.0,
      "text": "to predict what colors a\nblackbody would radiate"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 125060.0,
      "end_time": 126500.0,
      "text": "at certain temperatures."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 126500.0,
      "end_time": 128460.0,
      "text": "But the unfortunate happened."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 128460.00000000001,
      "end_time": 130449.00000000001,
      "text": "Their reasoning implied\nthat a blackbody"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 130449.00000000001,
      "end_time": 133880.0,
      "text": "should emit infinite amounts\nof ultraviolet light."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 133880.0,
      "end_time": 136920.0,
      "text": "They tried to apply their usual\nrules of Newtonian physics"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 136920.0,
      "end_time": 139010.0,
      "text": "and came up with nonsense."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 139010.0,
      "end_time": 142360.0,
      "text": "We now call this the\nultraviolet catastrophe."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 142360.0,
      "end_time": 144090.0,
      "text": "Oh, eye of a Newton."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 144090.0,
      "end_time": 146550.0,
      "text": "Something was very\nwrong with their work."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 146550.0,
      "end_time": 149500.0,
      "text": "A blackbody can't emit\ninfinite amounts of radiation"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 149500.0,
      "end_time": 151950.0,
      "text": "because that would violate\nlaws of conservation of energy."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 151950.0,
      "end_time": 155300.0,
      "text": "And just from, like,\nexperience, when you put toast"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 155300.0,
      "end_time": 157610.0,
      "text": "in your toaster,\nit doesn't promptly"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 157610.0,
      "end_time": 159330.0,
      "text": "burn your toast to smithereens."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 159330.0,
      "end_time": 161990.0,
      "text": "When observation contradicts\ntheory like this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 161990.0,
      "end_time": 164900.0,
      "text": "it often means there's\nsomething missing in the theory."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 164900.0,
      "end_time": 167670.0,
      "text": "Rayleigh and Jeans had\nfound a glaring error"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 167670.0,
      "end_time": 168830.0,
      "text": "in physics theory."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 168830.0,
      "end_time": 170330.0,
      "text": "Bum, bum, bum!"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 170330.0,
      "end_time": 173010.0,
      "text": "The same year that Rayleigh\nand Jeans published their work,"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 173010.0,
      "end_time": 175070.0,
      "text": "a German physicist,\nnamed Max Planck,"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 175070.0,
      "end_time": 177080.0,
      "text": "was studying radiation\nfor a different ."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 177080.0,
      "end_time": 179950.0,
      "text": "Reason he wanted to\nunderstand why heat always"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 179950.0,
      "end_time": 182650.0,
      "text": "flows from a hot object\nto a cold object."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 182650.0,
      "end_time": 184590.0,
      "text": "And in his quest to\nsolve that problem,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 184590.0,
      "end_time": 187090.0,
      "text": "he unintentionally\nfixed their error."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 187090.0,
      "end_time": 190040.0,
      "text": "He assumed that a blackbody\ncould only emit light"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 190040.0,
      "end_time": 192090.0,
      "text": "in discrete quantities."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 192090.0,
      "end_time": 195670.0,
      "text": "Its energy comes in chunks,\nequal to the frequency"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 195670.0,
      "end_time": 198950.0,
      "text": "of the light multiplied\nby this-- a number we now"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 198950.0,
      "end_time": 200650.0,
      "text": "know as Planck's Constant."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 200650.0,
      "end_time": 201840.0,
      "text": "This is weird."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 201840.0,
      "end_time": 203780.0,
      "text": "It would be like if\nyour faucet could only"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 203780.0,
      "end_time": 206180.0,
      "text": "pour full glasses\nof water at a time."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 206180.0,
      "end_time": 209050.0,
      "text": "But when Planck assumed\nlight was quantized,"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 209050.0,
      "end_time": 211570.0,
      "text": "theory matched with observation."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 211570.0,
      "end_time": 214600.0,
      "text": "He solved the\nultraviolet catastrophe."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 214600.0,
      "end_time": 215770.0,
      "text": "But here's the crazy part."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 215770.0,
      "end_time": 219410.0,
      "text": "Max Planck didn't immediately\nrealize how big of a deal"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 219410.0,
      "end_time": 220340.0,
      "text": "this was."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 220340.0,
      "end_time": 221485.0,
      "text": "Nobody did."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 221485.0,
      "end_time": 223110.0,
      "text": "He was just doing\nthe thing that we all"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 223110.0,
      "end_time": 225724.0,
      "text": "do with our math homework,\nwhen your answer doesn't match"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 225724.0,
      "end_time": 227140.0,
      "text": "the answer in the\nback of the book"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 227140.0,
      "end_time": 229500.0,
      "text": "so you just switch\na plus for a minus"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 229500.0,
      "end_time": 231100.0,
      "text": "but you're not really sure why."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 231100.0,
      "end_time": 232980.0,
      "text": "Planck didn't\nunderstand what his work"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 232980.0,
      "end_time": 234860.0,
      "text": "meant in the real world."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 234860.0,
      "end_time": 237750.0,
      "text": "It wasn't until a couple years\nlater that Einstein realized"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 237750.0,
      "end_time": 240990.0,
      "text": "that these packets of energy\nmeant that light wasn't just"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 240990.0,
      "end_time": 241730.0,
      "text": "a wave."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 241730.0,
      "end_time": 245530.0,
      "text": "It's made of particles\nthat we now call photons."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 245530.0,
      "end_time": 247440.0,
      "text": "So then physicists\nstarted thinking"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 247440.0,
      "end_time": 250710.0,
      "text": "about what this meant for\natoms that emit those photons,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 250710.0,
      "end_time": 254070.0,
      "text": "and The Theory of Quantum\nMechanics began to unfold."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 254070.0,
      "end_time": 257480.0,
      "text": "Atoms emit photons when\ntheir electrons lose energy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 257480.00000000003,
      "end_time": 262730.0,
      "text": "and so their electrons must lose\nenergy in chunks-- in quanta."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 262730.0,
      "end_time": 264470.0,
      "text": "Quantum mechanics."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 264470.0,
      "end_time": 267140.0,
      "text": "The consequences of\nMax Planck's discovery"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 267140.0,
      "end_time": 269760.0,
      "text": "that light comes in\nquanta, in packets,"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 269760.0,
      "end_time": 272800.0,
      "text": "snowballed into what we now\nknow as quantum mechanics."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 272800.0,
      "end_time": 275210.0,
      "text": "Quantum mechanics is bizarre."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 275210.0,
      "end_time": 277490.0,
      "text": "The microscopic world\njust misbehaves."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 277490.0,
      "end_time": 279940.0,
      "text": "Like, we're talking many\nbillions of times smaller"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 279940.0,
      "end_time": 281600.0,
      "text": "than the width of a human hair."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 281600.0,
      "end_time": 284530.0,
      "text": "For example, an electron\ncan be in multiple places"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 284530.0,
      "end_time": 285710.0,
      "text": "at the same time."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 285710.0,
      "end_time": 289970.0,
      "text": "In fact, an electron\nhas no precise location."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 289970.0,
      "end_time": 292530.0,
      "text": "But the weird thing is, when\nyou measure the electron,"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 292530.0,
      "end_time": 294950.0,
      "text": "you find it in a specific place."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 294950.0,
      "end_time": 297910.0,
      "text": "It's like it has no location\nuntil you measure it."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 297910.0,
      "end_time": 300710.0,
      "text": "This popular image\nof an atom is wrong."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 300710.0,
      "end_time": 302550.0,
      "text": "Instead, most of\nthe time it looks"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 302550.0,
      "end_time": 305850.0,
      "text": "like a cloud of probability\naround the proton."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 305850.0,
      "end_time": 308830.0,
      "text": "This cloud of probability\nis the electron."
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 308830.0,
      "end_time": 309790.0,
      "text": "Think about it."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 309790.0,
      "end_time": 311450.0,
      "text": "The particles that\nmake up your body"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 311450.0,
      "end_time": 313860.0,
      "text": "aren't a stack of solid objects."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 313860.0,
      "end_time": 316590.0,
      "text": "They're a collection\nof probability clouds."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 316590.0,
      "end_time": 321000.0,
      "text": "Quantum mechanics is\nunsatisfyingly unintuitive."
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 321000.0,
      "end_time": 323700.0,
      "text": "But time and again, it\nhas proven to be real,"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 323700.0,
      "end_time": 327370.0,
      "text": "applied in computer\nchips, lasers, even LEDs."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 327370.0,
      "end_time": 330020.0,
      "text": "An electron probability\ncloud is only"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 330020.0,
      "end_time": 333630.0,
      "text": "a nibble of the cookie\nthat is quantum weirdness."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 333630.0,
      "end_time": 336890.0,
      "text": "And after more than 100\nyears of study on the topic,"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 336890.0,
      "end_time": 338720.0,
      "text": "there's still more\nto learn, which"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 338720.0,
      "end_time": 341140.0,
      "text": "is why we're doing things\nlike colliding particles"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 341140.0,
      "end_time": 342770.0,
      "text": "at the Large Hadron Collider."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 342770.0,
      "end_time": 344470.0,
      "text": "Just as a small example."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 344470.0,
      "end_time": 347060.0,
      "text": "I love this story because\nit shows how important it"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 347060.0,
      "end_time": 348510.0,
      "text": "is to be wrong."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 348510.0,
      "end_time": 351720.0,
      "text": "Science isn't fixed\nfacts and figures."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 351720.0,
      "end_time": 354670.0,
      "text": "It's constantly being\nmodified and improved."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 354670.0,
      "end_time": 358360.0,
      "text": "Without Rayleigh uncovering\nthis huge theoretical error that"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 358360.0,
      "end_time": 361430.0,
      "text": "was the ultraviolet\ncatastrophe, physicists"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 361430.0,
      "end_time": 363210.0,
      "text": "may have never come\nup with the rules"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 363210.0,
      "end_time": 367180.0,
      "text": "to describe a brand new\ntiny, tiny universe."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 367180.0,
      "end_time": 370600.0,
      "text": "Thank you so much for\nwatching, and happy physicsing."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 370600.0,
      "end_time": 374250.0,
      "text": "[MUSIC PLAYING]"
    }
  ]
}